# ViLoLabs — Cloudflare Pages _redirects
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Rules are evaluated TOP-TO-BOTTOM, first match wins. Status 200 = rewrite
# (URL stays in the bar, target served). Client-side JS reads location.pathname
# and renders the slug-specific view.
#
# ⚠️ HARD-WON RULES OF THIS FILE (each was a production bug):
# 1. Rewrite targets must NOT contain ".html" — Cloudflare silently DROPS the
#    rule (e.g. "/worksheets/index.html" killed the slug catch-all → every
#    shared worksheet URL 404'd). Use the directory form "/worksheets/".
# 2. A splat like /worksheets/* swallows REAL files in that folder too. The
#    worksheet data files (worksheet-seo.js, seo-keywords.json) therefore live
#    in /assets/, NOT /worksheets/. Never put real assets under a splat path.

# The worksheet hub URL.  Public URL is /worksheet (singular). The file lives
# at worksheet.html — /worksheet resolves to it naturally via Cloudflare Pages
# Pretty URLs, no rewrite needed. Old /sheets and /sheets.html URLs still
# 301-redirect to /worksheet so existing bookmarks and incoming links work.
#
# 🚨 DO NOT re-add a `/worksheet → /sheets 200` rewrite here. A previous
# version of this file had exactly that plus the `/sheets → /worksheet 301`
# below, forming a rewrite-then-redirect loop. External browsers didn't see
# it (they only follow one hop) but env.ASSETS.fetch() inside the Pages
# Function at functions/worksheets/[slug].js processed the loop and returned
# 404. This broke every /worksheets/<slug> share URL in production while
# passing all local wrangler tests. The fix was to rename sheets.html →
# worksheet.html and delete the rewrite. Do not undo either.
/sheets                   /worksheet      301
/sheets/                  /worksheet      301
/sheets.html              /worksheet      301

# Pretty URLs for /worksheets/<slug>  →  handled by the Pages Function at
# functions/worksheets/[slug].js, which fetches the worksheet hub via
# env.ASSETS and stream-injects per-slug SEO meta via HTMLRewriter. The
# Function replaces the old `/worksheets/* /sheets 200` rewrite — never
# re-add that rule, it would PREEMPT the Function and break server-rendered SEO.
#
# The two normalization rules below still belong here: they redirect the
# bare path with/without trailing slash so /worksheets/ serves the static
# landing page (worksheets/index.html), not the Function.
/worksheets               /worksheets/    200
/worksheets/              /worksheets/    200

# Tool-share pretty URLs — /tools/<tool>/<slug>  →  serve /tools/<tool>.html
# (no real files live under these dirs, so the splat is safe here)
/tools/resize-image/*      /tools/resize-image      200
/tools/qr-generator/*      /tools/qr-generator      200
/tools/image-to-pdf/*      /tools/image-to-pdf      200
/tools/compress-image/*    /tools/compress-image    200
/tools/compress-pdf/*      /tools/compress-pdf      200
/tools/merge-pdf/*         /tools/merge-pdf         200
/tools/pdf-to-word/*       /tools/pdf-to-word       200
/tools/pdf-to-image/*      /tools/pdf-to-image      200

# (Add more redirects here as the site grows.)
